  "prompt": "What is one life hack so important you know that most of the people are unaware?",
  "response": "One simple yet powerful life hack that many people might be unaware of is utilizing the \"two-minute rule\" for productivity. The rule is straightforward: if a task will take two minutes or less to complete, do it immediately. \n\nHere\u2019s why it\u2019s so effective:\n1. **Reduces Procrastination**: Small tasks can pile up and lead to feeling overwhelmed. By tackling them right away, you prevent this buildup.\n2. **Boosts Efficiency**: Completing quick actions immediately can free up mental space and allow you to focus on larger, more complex tasks.\n3. **Creates Momentum**: Completing even minor tasks can build a sense of accomplishment and momentum, motivating you to continue working effectively throughout the day.\n4. **Habit Formation**: Consistently practicing the two-minute rule helps develop a habit of prompt action, which can translate into overall increased productivity.\n\nWhether it\u2019s answering an email, putting away a dish, or jotting down a quick note, applying the two-minute rule can lead to significant improvements in time management and efficiency.",
